    <p>Slang that becomes widely understood eventually enters the dictionary. SELFIE, BINGE (in the streaming sense), and FOMO have all made it into recent editions. These are often short, tile-efficient words that play well on tight boards and are unlikely to be challenged.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">How New Words Enter the Scrabble Dictionary</h2>

    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
